104607.name: Social expenditure on family (% of GDP) (OECD Stats (2019))
104607.description: Social expenditures on family include child allowances and credits, childcare support, income support during leave, and single parent payments.
104607.datasetName: Social expenditure by social policy area - OECD SOCX (2019)

source.name: Social expenditure by social policy area (SOCX) - OECD Stats (2019)
source.dataPublishedBy: OECD.Stat - The OECD Social Expenditure Database
source.additionalInfo: The OECD Social Expenditure Database groups benefits with a social purpose into 9 policy areas: old age, survivors, incapacity-related benefits, health, family, active labour market policies, unemployment, housing, and other social policy areas. Social spending on each of these areas is expressed as a percentage of a country's GDP. For further information see the 2019 SOCX manual.
